goals.question: What is the distribution of wildlife species involved in aircraft incidents?

goals.question: What is the distribution of aircraft makes and models involved in incidents?

goals.question: What is the distribution of the effect amount of damage caused by wildlife strikes?

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x=species_count.index, y=species_count.values, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Wildlife Species')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Incidents')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wildlife species involved in aircraft incidents?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.countplot(data=data, x='Aircraft_Make_Model', palette='viridis', order=data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts().index)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of aircraft makes and models involved in incidents?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Aircraft Make and Model')
    plt.ylabel('Incident Count')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Effect_Amount_of_damage', kde=True, color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.axvline(data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['Effect_Amount_of_damage'].median():.2f}")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the effect amount of damage caused by wildlife strikes?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.countplot(data=data, x='Phase_of_flight', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the phase of flight during which incidents occur?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Phase of Flight')
    plt.ylabel('Incident Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Phase of Flight', loc='upper right', labels=data['Phase_of_flight'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Cost_Total__', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    median_cost = data['Cost_Total__'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_cost, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_cost:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the total cost of incidents?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Total Cost of Incidents')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
